				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Wild Life: The Card Game" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Wild Life is a quick and fun competitive game for 2 to 5 players about making card sets of different animals that generate points at the end of each cycle or round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The main precepts of the game are: simple, fun, high interaction between players, and environmental awareness.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of your turn you will have 6 cards in hand and you will necessarily have to play 3.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has 4 types of animal cards: small, large, flying, and aquatic. Each one scores a different amount of points as long as they survive until the end of the cycle. In addition, you can use enhancer ecosystem cards that will multiply the points you'll get.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can mess with other players and this is where it gets interesting, for this you have 3 alternatives:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The predator which eliminates an animal from an opponent.&amp;#10;     The hunter who eliminates all animals of one type from a player.&amp;#10;     The catastrophe (fire or water pollution) that affects all players, including you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As you play and have fun you will develop environmental awareness.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All illustrations are handmade by Leo Cordoba who is also one of the designers of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;AWARDS &amp;amp; HONORS: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     2019: Zapada Ludica (Puebla City), 1st place board game design contest.&amp;#10;     2019: Official Game for Roll-A-Game Expo (Mexico), Top 5 finalist.&amp;#10;     2019: Roll-A-Game Expo (Mexico), 2nd place board game design contest.&amp;#10;     2020: Mega XP (Mexico), 1st place board game design contest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
